  "prompt": "How and how much is announcer Bruce Buffer of MMA Octagon paid?",
  "response": "Bruce Buffer, known as the \"Veteran Voice of the Octagon\" for the UFC, is well-compensated for his role as the lead announcer. While the exact details of his contract are not publicly disclosed, estimates suggest he earns between $50,000 to $100,000 per event. For major events like pay-per-view fights, his earnings might be on the higher end of that spectrum. Additionally, Bruce Buffer's income is supplemented by his merchandise, public appearances, and other business ventures related to his brand. His distinctive announcing style and long-standing career in the UFC contribute to his high earning potential in the mixed martial arts industry.",
